Commentary Text: Chahar to Tom Curran, no run, Curran looks shell-shocked as he's given out caught behind, wants a review and realises to his horror that he can't review. Tewatia and that plumb LBW call had it wasted. Hang on! I don't think that even carried to MS - the two umpires chatted for a while and then sent Curran on his way, but replays suggest that the ball might not have carried. Even worse - I don't even think Curran has edged it, it seemed to have gone off the thigh-pad. They are checking for the catch though - it's a fair delivery, nips back in and has only clipped the thigh-pad, bounced clearly in front of MS and NOT OUT is the call. For once, technology has been well used and Curran can resume batting. Still, would the decision been reversed had the ball carried? That's for another day though, short of a length and nipping back in, Curran was looking to pull and missed, clipped the top of the thigh-pad and bounced in front of MS

Commentary Text: Chawla to Uthappa, out Caught by du Plessis!! A chance and Faf has grabbed it cleanly. Redemption for Piyush, he struggled in the first two overs, but is pulling things back a touch. A poor start for Uthappa in Royals colours - came down the track, got close to the ball and drilled the drive - went flat, hard and straight to long-off. Commentary Text: Ngidi to Smith, out Miller Run Out!! 1 run completed. Appeal for a run-out at the bowler's end, Miller dived, has it saved him? A flat throw and a good pick-up. No, the dive's not good enough and Miller falls for a diamond duck on his Royals debut. Unfortunate way to get dismissed - it didn't help that Miller lost his bat as well, could have saved him else. On a length and at the stumps, worked in front of square on the on-side and it was Smith's call for the second. Miller responded well, but lost his bat as he dived - good throw from Gaikwad and Kedar was at hand to break the stumps. Miller run out (Ruturaj Gaikwad/Kedar Jadhav) 0(0)

Commentary Text: Ngidi to Samson, out Caught by Chahar!! That is the end of the Samson show - he's furious with himself as he walks back. Would have been a wide had he let it go - but the adrenaline was pumping and he couldn't hold back - went chasing after that and lifted it towards deep cover - Chahar ran in, took it awkwardly around his chest, reverse cupped - it threatened to pop out, but he manages to clutch it safely. Was the slower short ball and Samson didn't have the pace on the shot. Some relief for the CSKians, they clearly looked rattled. Samson c Chahar b Ngidi 74(32) [4s-1 6s-9]

Commentary Text: Rahul Tewatia to Watson, out Bowled!! The pull, the famed Watson pull, has brought about his downfall. Problem is the length isn't short at all. He's just trying to manufacture it out of nothing. Fails badly as this skids through onto his back pad and crashes into leg stump. May have been fooled by the trajectory actually. Tewatia kept it quite flat, pushing it through off the front of his hand. May have caused him to believe it was shorter than it was. Watson's furious with himself. Watson b Rahul Tewatia 33(21) [4s-1 6s-4]
